title: Prime Ministers of Canada
snippet: This page provides general details on Canada's prime ministers since 1867.

title: List of prime ministers of Canada - Wikipedia
snippet: Two prime ministers have died in office: John A. Macdonald (1867–1873, 1878–1891) and John Thompson (1892–1894), both of natural causes. All others have resigned, either after losing an election or upon retirement.

title: Government Ministries and Prime Ministers of Canada Since 1867 - House of Commons Procedure and Practice, Third edition, 2017 - ProceduralInfo - House of Commons of Canada
snippet: On October 12, 1917, Prime Minister Sir Robert Borden formed a Ministry, known as the Unionist government, which brought together Liberal-Conservative and Liberal Members of Parliament who supported conscription during World War I. See Robert Craig Brown, Robert Laird Borden: A Biography, vol.
